this is a template for "OmniCode Folder Metadata":
    keyed as "B-word-omni-seed-folder"
    following "3-Block Folder Structure"

this template classifies as:
    word (1) when "folder contains definitions, specifications, source of truth"
    work (0) when "folder contains implementations, instances, active development"
    fruit (-1) when "folder contains derivations, outputs, generated artifacts"

this template derives from:
    original (1) when "establishing new folder pattern"
    derived (0) from "B-word-omni-seed-data-3block"
    variant (-1) when "intentionally departing from standard"
    documented at "bereshit/word/omni/seed/"

this template strictness is:
    tight (1) meaning "Follow exactly - 3-block structure, required sections"
    guided (0) meaning "Adapt thoughtfully - folder-specific values within structure"
    free (-1) meaning "Principles only - teaching comments, placeholders"

to use this template:
    copy as root.omni into the folder being defined
    replace [bracketed] placeholders with actual content
    change pragma from "template" to "folder" when complete
    remove this preamble section when adapted

    meaning "Folder metadata - stored truth about folder identity and structure"
    teaching "Folders are data about organization - 3-block declares what the folder IS"

